OOC (Out-Of-Character) CHANNEL

Syntax: ooc <message>
        ooc off
        ooc on

The OOC channel is a global out-of-character communication channel.
Messages sent via OOC are heard by all players on the MUD regardless of
location or language.  It is explicitly for player-to-player communication
outside the game's fiction.

Use OOC for:
  - Questions about game mechanics
  - Asking for help finding something
  - Casual conversation between players
  - Reporting bugs or issues to staff

Do NOT use OOC for:
  - In-character roleplay (use 'say', 'tell', or 'shout' instead)
  - Harassment or abuse

TOGGLE
  ooc off      stops you from receiving OOC messages (you go deaf to the channel)
  ooc on       re-enables OOC reception

You can still SEND on OOC while deaf; you just will not receive others' replies.

See also: say, tell, shout, radio
